registerEntry.entryText: PROPRIETOR: DIANE HARDY and NEIL HARDY of 91 South Hill Avenue, MANCHESTER, M41 8TZ.
The Freehold land shown edged with red on the plan of the above title filed at the Registry and being 91 South Hill Avenue, MANCHESTER (M41 8TZ).

entryText: A Deed of Agreement affecting the land in this title and other land dated 15 July 1988 made between (1) Manchester City Council and (2) David Michael Harrison and Emma Louise Taylor contains the following covenants:-

The Applicants hereby jointly and severally COVENANT that if they are granted planning permission in accordance with their application numbered 88/0038 (whether or not such permission is granted subject to conditions) the internal floorspace excluding garages of the residential units to be built on the site will not exceed 660 square feet and there will be no extensions to the residential units in the future.

A Conveyance of the land in this title and other land dated 28 April 1989 made between (1) David Michael Harrison and Emma Louise Taylor (Vendors) and (2) Andrew James Wilson (Purchaser) contains the following covenants:-

"THE PURCHASER hereby covenants with the Vendors and each of them not to use the property hereby conveyed or allow the same to be so used so as to cause a nuisance or annoyance to the owner or occupier for the time being of the Retained Property provided that this covenant shall not in any way restrict or prevent the Purchaser from developing the property hereby conveyed for residential occupation and use."
The land is subject to the following rights reserved by the Conveyance dated 28 April 1989 referred to above:-
"Subject as provided in the said First Schedule
EXCEPTING AND RESERVING unto the Vendors and their successors in title owners for the time being of the Vendors Retained Property:-

(a) the right (subject to obtaining all necessary Local Authority approval) to connect into the foul sewer and surface water drain to be laid by the Purchaser in or through the property hereby conveyed (such connections to be made at the Vendors expense and in such position as shall be approved by the Purchaser) and thereafter a right to use the said foul sewer and surface water drain for the free and uninterrupted passage and running of water and sewerage but without any warranty by the Purchaser that such sewer and drain shall be sufficient capacity as to permit the exercise of such rights

(b) the right upon reasonably prior notice (except in the case of emergency) to enter upon the Property hereby conveyed so far as may be necessary for the purpose of inspecting cleansing maintaining repairing and renewing the connections to be made to the foul sewer and surface water drain in accordance with sub-clause (a) above and also the fence or any other boundary structure to be erected by the Vendors in accordance with the covenant on their part herein contained."

The land is subject to the following rights granted by a Transfer of an Electricity Sub-Station dated 9 July 1990 made between (1) Andrew James Wilson (Transferor) and (2) Electricity North West Limited (Company):-
Together with any rights appurent to that property as may be set out in the Second Schedule
THE RIGHTS APPURTENANT TO THE PROPERTY TRANSFERRED
(iv) A right to lay electric lines within the meaning of Section 64 of the Electricity Act 1989

(i)  In the position indicated on the attached plan and shown by broken red lines together also to erect and maintain a pole and stay together with all necessary guards wires and appliances as shown on the said plan

(v)  A right to break up the surface of any of the above land roads or footpaths for the purpose of laying repairing and maintaining the electric lines doing as little damage as possible and making good any damage caused.
The said Transfer also contains the following covenants by the Transferor:-
The Transferor covenants with the Company and its successors in title to observe and perform the matters set out in the Third Schedule
THE THIRD SCHEDULE
COVENANTS TO BE OBSERVED BY THE TRANSFEROR:
(i)    To indemnify the Company against all costs charges and expenses involved in the construction and adoption of any roads and footpaths on the adjoining estate

(ii)   Not at any time after the date of this Deed to excavate under or alter the level of ground over nor construct or permit to be constructed any building or structure or erection of any kind whatsoever over or within one metre on either side of the route of the electric lines referred to in The Second Schedule to this Transfer other than any buildings structures or erections marked on the attached plan

(iii)  Not to erect or cause or permit to be erected any building structure or other erection plant or materials in such proximity to the said sty as to cause damage or danger to the same or anyone working thereon.
NOTE: The red broken lines referred to are shown by a blue broken line on the filed plan so far as they affect the land in this title.
A Transfer of the land in this title dated 21 September 1990 made between (1) Andrew James Wilson and (2) Michael Thompson and Sarah Johnson contains restrictive covenants.
NOTE: Original filed.

The electronic official copy of the register follows this message.

Please note that this is the only official copy we will issue. We will not issue a paper official copy.

Official copy of register of title

Title number TF142222    Edition date 13.07.2025

- This official copy shows the entries on the register of title on 13 July 2025 at 08:37:16.
- This date must be quoted as the "search from date" in any official search application based on this copy.
- The date at the beginning of an entry is the date on which the entry was made in the register.
- Issued on 13 Jul 2025.
- Under s.67 of the Land Registration Act 2002, this copy is admissible in evidence to the same extent as the original.
- This title is dealt with by HM Land Registry, Gloucester Office.

This register describes the land and estate comprised in the title.

CITY OF BRISTOL

definitions: 1.1 Accessway means the footpath or driveway shown cross hatched on the Plan.
1.2 Easement Strip means the drainage easement strip shown on the Plan (if any).
1.3 Estate includes all the land now or formerly comprised in or subsequently added to the above title and on which the Seller is carrying out a residential development.

1.4 Estate Roads includes the carriageways footpaths and verges on the Estate and their intended sites which serve the Property and which are intended to become maintainable at public expense part of which are shown hatched on the Plan.

1.5 Estate Sewers means the main foul and surface water sewers and any accessories as defined by Section 219 of the Water Industry Act 1991 now or within the Perpetuity Period constructed within the Estate which are intended to become sewers maintainable at the public expense.
1.6 Perpetuity Period means the period of 80 years from 1st January 2003.
1.7 Plan means the plan annexed hereto.
1.8 Projections includes foundations chimneys flues eaves guttering drainpipes fence posts wall piers and similar projections now or within the Perpetuity Period constructed within the Estate.
1.9 Property means the land shown edged red on the Plan being part of the land in the above title.
1.10 Public Authority includes local authorities and all water companies statutory corporations and authorities exercising statutory rights or obligations.
1.11 Service Media includes all drains pipes wires cables conducting media and apparatus for surface and foul water drainage and other specified services constructed on the Estate.
1.12 Water Company means the water company which will adopt the Estate Sewers and its successors in title.

1.13 Dominant Tenement means the undertaking of the water company within its area as particularised in the Instrument of Appointment under the Water Act 1989 and in particular the Estate Sewers together with related land and rights.
1.14 Woodland means the area of public open space indicated on the Plan to be maintained by the Buyer (Plots 16, 38 to 44 only).
rightsGrantedForTheBenefitOfTheProperty: 1. A right of way at all times for all lawful purposes on foot over the footpaths and with vehicles over the carriageways of the Estate Roads.

2. A right of way at all times for all lawful purposes on foot over the footpaths or on foot or with vehicles over the driveway comprising the Accessway on the Estate which serves the Property but is not edged red on the Plan (if any).
3. The right to use the Estate Sewers for the passage of water and sewage.
4. The right to use inspect maintain and renew any Service Media on the Estate which serve the Property.
5. The right of support and protection from any adjoining parts of the Estate for the Property including any buildings now or to be constructed by the Seller on the Property.
6. The right to keep and use on adjoining parts of the Estate any Projections from the Property as constructed by the Seller.

7. The right to enter upon adjoining parts of the Estate to inspect maintain or renew any part of the Property or the Service Media or Accessway (if any) serving the Property, subject to the proviso that none of the rights shall apply to electricity sub-station(s) on the Estate.
rightsReservedForTheBenefitOfOtherLand: 1. A right of way at all times and for all purposes over the Accessway (if any) on the Property which serves any other part of the Estate or any land adjoining the Estate.
2. The right to retain connect to and use inspect maintain and renew any Service Media or Estate Sewers which cross the Property.
3. The right of support and protection from the Property and any buildings on the Property for the Estate and any buildings now or to be constructed by the Seller on the Estate.
4. The right to keep and use on the Property any Projections from any buildings on the Estate now or to be constructed by the Seller on the Estate.
5. The right to enter on the Property to inspect maintain or renew any part of the Estate adjoining the Property or the Service Media.
6. The right for the Seller or Public Authority to enter the Property to alter existing Service Media and to lay new Service Media.

7. The right for the Seller or Public Authority to erect scaffolding and construct adjoining buildings walls or fences relating to adjoining buildings on the Estate; to enforce compliance with covenants and to comply with public authority requirements.
restrictiveCovenantsByTheTransferee: 1. Not to use the Property for any purpose other than as or incidental to one private residential dwelling and not for any trade or business.
2. Not to erect or construct any building or other structure (except for good quality domestic sheds and greenhouses) without the prior consent in writing of the Seller.
3. Not to erect any walls fences or other structures nor allow hedges to grow on the Property between any building on the Property and the Estate Roads.
4. Not to allow the Property boundary fences walls or hedges to fall into disrepair and to keep repaired.
5. Not to cut down damage neglect or remove any existing tree or hedge on the Property or any other plant planted pursuant to Public Authority requirements.
6. Not to do or permit to be done on the Property anything which may be a nuisance or cause damage to the Seller or to owners tenants or occupiers of neighbouring property.

7. Not to erect or exhibit hoarding structure notice board or sign for advertising except as permitted after the Seller's sales office is permanently closed (one notice not exceeding half square metre permitted).
8. Not to keep or feed animals other than normal household domestic pets.
9. Not to park any commercial vehicle caravan or boat on the Property between any building on the Property and the Estate Road.
10. Not to park on or obstruct the Estate Roads or Accessway (if any).
11. Not to erect aerials or satellite dishes on front elevations until the Seller has completed sale of the last dwellinghouse on the Estate.
12. Not without prior written consent of the Public Authority to erect or place any structure on the visibility splay or service strip shown on the Plan and to maintain it as grassed area.

13. Not to do anything which may impede adoption or vesting in the Public Authority of Estate Roads Estate Sewers or Service Media, and not to cause loss or damage to Estate Roads Estate Sewers or Service Media or interfere with them.
14. Not to alter within three years the existing colour of the whole or any part of the exterior of the dwellinghouse on the Property.
15. Not to cut down damage neglect or remove the Woodland nor erect walls fences or other structures on the Woodland.
otherProvisions: PART 6: Positive covenants by the Seller to construct and maintain Estate Roads and Estate Sewers to the requirements of the Public Authority and indemnify Buyer until adoption.

PART 7: Rights reserved for the benefit of the Water Company and the Dominant Tenement including rights of access to the Easement Strip, to enter to excavate, erect markers, tip soil and erect/maintain works necessary for Estate Sewers and Service Media.

Covenants for the benefit of the Water Company impose obligations on the Buyer not to endanger or damage the Estate Sewers, not to adversely affect flow, not to erect structures within the Easement Strip, not to withdraw support, not to carry out piling or percussive works, not to alter ground levels within the Easement Strip, and not to plant trees or shrubs within the Easement Strip.
The Property is clearly defined on the attached plan and shown edged red (plan included).
